text: Maybe this is just me, but I would like to tell you all my experience watching this movie: It was 1 a.m., and I was on the fence whether or not to watch one more movie. I was very impulsive in choosing this movie because the only criteria was to have Tom Holland in it. I didn‚Äôt watch the trailer, just pressed play. Fast forward TWO HOURS AND A HALF. I was watching the last scene with the words popping up desperately trying to read them with my bleary vision and extremely tired body. After the movie ended I probably sat there for five minutes staring in the dark left only with anger, dismay, and frustration. I believe I started to laugh hysterically. To this day, I am adamant that this was the worst f***ing movie I ever watched and it left me soulless and depressed. I only feel worse for the people who payed money to watch it in theaters.
